text:
80 Eighth Avenue, at the N.E. corner of West 14th Street (County Trust Co. Building) general view eastward.

An eastward view along 14th (right) and 15th (left) Streets, towards and across 7th and 6th Avenues. The prominent buildings in the foreground are the 9 story Convent of Jesus Mary (No. 222 West 15th Street), and a new apartment house (No. 72-7th Avenue). To the left of the latter appears the 7 story building occupied by the printing house, Street and Smith.

Thru this foreground area on a diagonal ran the Colonial thoroughfare "Southampton Road." Fitz Roy Road branched off to the north from a point in the backyards at the lower edge.

June 18, 1931

P. L. Sperr
title: General view - [Manhattan] - County Trust Company Building.
